Texas Instruments Inc said constructionwill begin in April on a new plant near Denton, Texas, on 193acres owned by the company.    It said the plant will initially employ between 1,000 and1,500 people, and will be used by its Defense Systems andElectronics Group for producing electronic equipemnt. The plantis expected to be operational in late 1988.    Separately, the company said it leased about 185,000 squarefeet of a complex in Texas for its Defense Systems group. Itplans to transfer about 700 employees to work at the site bythe third quarter of 1987. Reuter&#3;